did.abstract: Contains records documenting the history of the Medicine Bow National Forest in Wyoming.

bioghist.head: History of Medicine Bow National Forest
bioghist.p: The Medicine Bow National Forest (MBNF) of southeastern Wyoming was created in 1902.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Collection contains correspondence, reports, newspaper clippings, maps, blueprints, photographs, and news releases on a variety of issues pertinent to the Medicine Bow National Forest including the installment of telephone lines, fire control, general administrative affairs, place names of land within the MBNF, grazing, mineral and timber rights within the MBNF, watersheds, wildlife management, and recreational activities. Collection also contains biographical information on Forest Service employees who were employed at the MBNF (1912-1958) and biographical information on early residents of Albany and Carbon counties and Laramie, Wyoming (1921- 1952). There are also maps of the MBNF; newspapers clippings; and photographs of ranger districts, campgrounds, timber cutting and Forest Service employees.

accessrestrict.head: Access Restrictions
accessrestrict.p: There are no access restrictions on the materials for research purposes, and the collection is open to the public.

userestrict.head: Copyright Information
userestrict.p: The researcher assumes full responsibility for observing all copyright, property, and libel laws as they apply.

relatedmaterial.head: Related Materials
relatedmaterial.p: There are no known other archival collections created by Medicine Bow National Forest at the date of processing.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: This material was received from the Medicine Bow National Forest Office.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: The collection was processed by Laura Uglean Jackson in July 2011.

scopecontent.p: Contains reports, correspondence, memoranda, news clippings and news releases on a variety of issues, topics, and locations of MBNF. Information on financials, personnel, and other administrative operations can also be found in this series. There are also maps, a field journal, and a run of the MBNF's weekly newsletter (1975-1978).

scopecontent.p: Contains letters and memos to and from MBNF personnel on a variety of topics including homesteading, fires, recreation, and general administrative operations.
Primarily contains newspaper clippings about MBNF issues and activities, but also includes MBNF publications such as pamphlets.

This set of photographs is organized by a hierarchical filing structure created by the MBNF. It contains hundreds of photographs and negatives of the MBNF, including people and personnel; lumber and timber operations; recreational activities such as skiing, picnicking and fishing; plants and animals; and forest fire damage, equipment, and prevention.
